    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terres</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States.</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince, Haiti</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9,
                                        1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 153.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 102, of the 21st ultimo, relative to the attachment on the
                            second installment of the indemnity awarded to Richard Allen.</p>
                <p>In accordance with your instructions, I have transmitted to the secretary
                            of state for foreign affairs the views of the Department on the
                            subject.</p>
                <p>I, however, beg leave to inform you that on the 15th ultimo an
                            arrangement was made between Messrs. Devot and Allen by which the former
                            agreed to raise the attachment, and that the amount was duly turned over
                            to this legation by the National Bank of Haiti.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Terres.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
